      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead-big">Person Specification</span></p>
<p><strong>Please note: The criteria below will be assessed through the application (a), a set task (t), or interview (i) Please ensure that all criteria marked (a) are explicitly addressed in your application form</strong></p>
<table border="0" width="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th width="331">
<h3>Person Specification – Essential</h3>
</th>
<th width="350">
<h3>Person Specification – Desirable</h3>
</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>A first degree in a relevant subject (a)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Experience of working on collaborative projects between industry and academia and actively seeking out and undertaking these in line with HEI expectations (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Completed (or near completion) PhD in a relevant subject area OR relevant postgraduate qualification and significant relevant professional/industry experience (a)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p> Experience of marking student assignments against agreed learning outcomes (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Necessary knowledge and expertise required to teach across a variety of business law modules (a&amp;t)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Necessary knowledge and expertise to teach dispute resolution subjects such as mediation and negotiation (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Network of relevant industry connections that will benefit the student experience (a)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Necessary knowledge and expertise to design and deliver new modules on employment and labour law (a&amp;t)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Passionate about teaching and learning and committed to enhancing the student experience (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Experience of public engagement and/or knowledge exchange activity (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Motivates self and colleagues effectively, setting clear objectives to manage performance (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>A scholarship interest related to fair work and ethical business (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Communicates effectively orally and in writing, adapting the message for a diverse audience in an inclusive and accessible way (a&amp;i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Experience of supervising dissertations and final major projects - academic and/or practice-based (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Plans, prioritises, and manages resources effectively to achieve long term objectives (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Experience of providing pastoral and academic support to undergraduate and postgraduate students (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Builds effective teams, networks or communities of practice and fosters constructive cross team collaboration (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Experience in using IT in learning and teaching using a recognised virtual learning platform to support learning (i)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Exhibits flexibility and willingness to respond positively to changing priorities within the division, school and university (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Fellowship of the Higher Education Academy, or willingness to work towards Fellowship on appointment (a)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>A positive attitude towards challenging situations, providing practical solutions to new or unique problems (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Experience of applying innovative approaches in teaching and learning to enhance student experience and attainment</p>
<p> (t&amp;i)</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="331">
<p>Ability to work productively within an open plan office environment (i)</p>
</td>
<td width="350">
<p>Familiarity with curriculum design, assessment, and quality assurance practices in UK HE (t)</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>]]></Value>
