    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead">Role Purpose</span></p>
<p>The primary purpose of this role is to work collaboratively with an established team of academics to deliver undergraduate and postgraduate courses in the division of Business, Enterprise and Management. In addition to a broad knowledge and understanding of the field of business law the post holder is also expected to provide the division with specific knowledge and expertise regarding either employment law, mediation, or negotiation. In addition to their teaching responsibilities at both undergraduate and postgraduate level, the post holder will also be required to contribute towards the administrative and operational running of the division, undertake scholarship, and generate income.    </p>]]></Value>
